## Part 5 — Architecture

<!-- Inline question: <multipleChoice> with parens-shorthand -->
<assignment id=cpu-pipeline>
### Pipeline stages
A classic 5-stage RISC pipeline orders its stages as:

<multipleChoice id=cpu-pipeline>
  ( ) Fetch → Decode → Memory → Execute → Writeback
  (x) Fetch → Decode → Execute → Memory → Writeback
  ( ) Decode → Fetch → Execute → Writeback → Memory
  ( ) Fetch → Execute → Decode → Memory → Writeback
</multipleChoice>
</assignment>

<!-- Inline question: numeric with an expression-slot answer -->
<assignment id=binary-add>
### Add the two numbers
What is **0b1010** plus **0b0110**, in decimal?

<numeric id=binary-add answer={0b1010 + 0b0110} tolerance=0/>
</assignment>

